Answer: Initialization is the process of assigning a value to a variable for the first time after it has been declared. Example:

```java
int b;
b = 10;
```

The statement b = 10; represents initialization because the variable receives its first value.

Answer: Variable reassignment is the process of assigning a new value to a variable after it has already been initialized. Example:

```java
int b = 10;
b = 999;
```

Here, the second assignment changes the existing value stored in the variable. This process is called reassignment.
